This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with natural language processing (NLP) and word representations. The use of hidden Markov models (HMMs) and syntactic dependency trees also suggests a focus on computational linguistics. 

It is also likely to belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) as the paper discusses unsupervised learning and representation learning methods. 

cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another possible sub-category as the paper deals with machine learning techniques applied to NLP tasks. 

cs.SD (Sound) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) are less likely but still possible sub-categories as the paper deals with models and algorithms for NLP tasks, which could potentially involve sound processing or neural networks.
